@NODE "Main" "SuperMANPPC ©2000-2004 by J.T. Steichen"
@TOC  "Contents"
@NEXT "Controls"

   @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} (2.0) is a GUI for finding & displaying text files, nroff files, 
   or @{AmigaGuide} files.  Change the @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"} & you can select which files
   to list & choose from.  You can also set the program that displays the 
   file using the @{" FileViewer " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType, or by sel-
   ecting one of the viewing commands from the @{B}Commands@{UB} ListView gadget.  
   Some keys can be used to perform the same functions as certain gadgets 
   (see @{" Hidden Keys " LINK "KeyStrokes"} ).

   @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} was written using @{FG SHINE}GadToolsBox V37.300 & SAS-C V6.58.@{FG TEXT}
   
   @{" The Author " LINK "Author"}

   @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} requires a @{FG SHINE}PowerPC@{FG TEXT} CPU or better, a working version of
   nroff (or an equivalent) & the @{FG SHINE}multiview@{FG TEXT} program.
    
   @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} also requires that you have @{B}ENVARC:@{UB} assigned to wherever
   your Environmental variables are kept.  This is normally defined as:
@{FG SHINE}
      Assign ENVARC: System:Prefs/Env-Archive/ 
@{FG TEXT}
   in your @{B}S:Startup-Sequence@{UB} file.

   There is special support & functionality for the usage of nroff as a
   *NIX manual page displayer.  This is necessary because nroff does NOT
   open a console or window for itself.  There are two @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"} for this
   in the icon, as well as an entry in the @{B}Commands:@{UB} ListView.
@{FG SHINE}
   HISTORY @{FG TEXT}
      2.0 - Added AmigaOS4 & PPC (gcc) support. 
      1.0 - First release to aminet.
      
   @{B}SEE ALSO,@{UB}   @{" Tutorial " LINK "Tutorial"}, @{" Document Controls " LINK "Controls"},
             @{" Directory Controls " LINK "DirControls"}, @{" Menu items " LINK "Menus"},
             @{" nroff manual " LINK "nroff.guide/Main"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Layout" "SuperMANPPC progam layout:"
@PREV "Main"

   This is the way the installer program will place the files in your
   
   hard disk (& the places that @{BOLD SuperMAN} expects to find them): 

   Assuming you placed @{B}SuperMANPPC@{UB} in a directory called DH0:SuperMan/

   DH0:SuperMan/SuperMANPPC
   DH0:SuperMan/SuperMANPPC.info
   DH0:SuperMan/CommandsList.txt
   DH0:SuperMan/DocsDirList.txt
   DH0:SuperMan/SuperMAN.guide
   DH0:SuperMan/nroff.guide

   ENV:TMACDIR              TMACDIR contains a directory specification for where
   ENVARC:TMACDIR           nroff can find its macro files.
   
   C:nroff     (see @{" NRoffCommand ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"})
   C:multiview (or somewhere else in your command path)
   C:delete

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DirControls" "SuperMANPPC Directory Controls:"
@PREV "Controls"
@NEXT "Main"
     @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} allows you to keep track of which directories have your
   
   document files.  The main controls are
   
   the @{BOLD Document Directories:} ListView Gadget, the @{B}@{U}A@{UU}dd Dir@{UB}

   button, the @{B}Remove Dir@{UB} button & the @{B}@{U}C@{UU}hange Dir@{UB} button.  
    
   Click on the directory in the ListView gadget that you wish to use, then
   
   press the @{B}@{U}C@{UU}hange Dir@{UB} button & release it.
   
     You can add an entry by typing in a pathname in the string gadget 
     
   below the ListView gadget or by selecting one with the ASL button gadget
   
   to the right of the string gadget, then pressing & releasing the @{B}@{U}A@{UU}dd Dir@{UB}
   
   button gadget.

     You can remove an entry by Selecting one from the ListView gadget, 
     
   then pressing & releasing the @{B}Remove Dir@{UB} button gadget.
   @{FG SHINE}
   WARNING:  There is no Undo for removed directories! @{FG TEXT}

     You can Change the directory by Selecting an entry in the @{B}Document
     
   Directories@{UB} ListView gadget, or by typing in a pathname in the string 
     
   gadget below the ListView gadget, or by selecting one with the ASL 
   
   button gadget to the right of the string gadget, then pressing & 
   
   releasing the @{B}@{U}C@{UU}hange Dir@{UB} button gadget.

   See Also, @{" Document Controls " LINK "Controls"},
             @{" Menu items " LINK "Menus"}   

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Controls" "SuperMANPPC Document Controls:"
@PREV "Main"
     @{BOLD SuperMANPPC} has very few controls to discuss.  The main controls the
   
   User really has to use are the @{BOLD Documents:} ListView Gadget, and the
    
   @{BOLD Commands:} ListView Gadget.

   Click on the document in the ListView gadget that you wish

   to examine, then click on an entry in the @{B}Commands:@{UB} ListView that 
    
   can show the type of file selected.

     You can change the directory to find your documents in with the 
   
   @{B}@{U}C@{UU}hange Dir@{UB} button gadget, or by directly typing in the path & filename

   you're looking for in the @{BOLD "File Name:"} string gadget.  There is also
    
   a graphic button next to the @{BOLD "File Name:"} string gadget that will bring up

   the ASL File Requester, allowing you to browse the file system & find the

   document you wish to view.  @{FG SHINE}You exit the program by 
   
   pressing & releasing the Close Window gadget located in the upper left 
   
   corner of the GUI.@{FG TEXT}

   See Also, @{" Document Directory Controls " LINK "DirControls"},
             @{" Menu items " LINK "Menus"}   

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tutorial" "SuperMANPPC tutorial:"

   Here is how to perform the basic operation of viewing a file:
   
   1. Click on a document directory in the @{B}Document Directories:@{UB} ListView.
      You can also enter a directory in the string gadget beneath the
      @{B}Document Directories:@{UB} ListView, or press & release the ASL button next
      to the string gadget.
         
   2. Press & Release the @{B}@{U}C@{UU}hange Dir@{UB} button gadget. 

   3. Click on a document in the @{B}Documents:@{UB} ListView.
      You can also enter a document in the string gadget beneath the
      @{B}Documents:@{UB} ListView, or press & release the ASL button next
      to the string gadget.

   4. Click on a command in the @{B}Commands:@{UB} ListView.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Menus" "SuperMANPPC Menu Items:"
   
   There are two menus for the program, @{B}PREFERENCES & HELP@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}    
   PREFERENCES             HELP @{FG TEXT}
    
    @{" Add Command.. " LINK "AddCommand"}      @{" SuperMAN.guide... " LINK "SuperMAN"}

    @{" Set Startup Dir.. " LINK "SetStartup"}      @{" NRoff.guide... " LINK "NRoff"}
    
    @{" Set Editor Command.. " LINK "SetEditor"}
    
    @{" Set File Filter.. " LINK "SetFilter"}
    
    @{" Set Macro EnvVar.. " LINK "SetMacro"}

    SEE ALSO @{" Hidden Keystrokes " LINK "KeyStrokes"}    

@ENDNODE

@NODE "KeyStrokes" "KeyStrokes available to SuperMANPPC:"

   There are some keystrokes that are not obvious in the GUI:
   
   i or I        - Displays a Requester with some information about SuperMANPPC.

   q, Q, x, or X - Equivalent to clicking on the Close Window Gadget.
                   (You exit SuperMANPPC).

   e or E        - Equivalent to clicking on the @{U}E@{UU}dit File Button Gadget.

   c or C        - Equivalent to clicking on the @{U}C@{UU}hange Dir File Button Gadget.

   a or A        - Equivalent to clicking on the @{U}A@{UU}dd Dir Button Gadget.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "AddCommand" "Add Command.. Menu Item:"

   This is how you add commands to the @{B}Commands@{UB} ListView gadget from within
   
   the @{B}SuperMANPPC@{UB} program.  You can also edit the file specified by the
   
   @{" CmdListFile " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType using your favorite text editor.

   @{B}SuperMANPPC@{UB} does @{B}NOT@{UB} allow you to remove any commands inside the program.
   
   This capability is purposefully omitted so that you don't accidentally
   
   remove commands.  You have to edit the @{" CmdListFile " LINK "ToolTypes"} outside of the 
   
   program, if you wish to delete or change command entries.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SetStartup" "Set Startup Dir... Menu Item:"

   This menuitem will change the @{FG SHINE}ParentDir@{FG TEXT} ToolType.

   This will only affect how the program starts up the next time you 
   
   use it.

   See Also, @{" ParentDir ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SetViewer" "Set Viewer Command... Menu Item:"

   This menuitem will change @{FG SHINE}FileViewer@{FG TEXT} ToolType, which is then used to 
   
   view any files that you select.  Some recommended values for this are:
   
      multiview              (Default)
   
      MuchMore               (Use multiview instead!)
    
   See Also, @{" FileViewer ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SetEditor" "Set Editor Command... Menu Item:"

   This menuitem will change @{FG SHINE}FileEditor@{FG TEXT} ToolType.

   See Also, @{" FileEditor ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SetFilter" "Set File Filter... Menu Item:"

   This menuitem will change @{FG SHINE}FileExtFilter@{FG TEXT} ToolType.

   Be careful with the @{BOLD FileExtFilter} ToolType.  The ASL File 
    
   Requester & AmigaDOS C functions used within the program expect the 
   
   parentheses to be around the expression if you use the @{FG SHINE}@{B}|@{UB}@{FG TEXT} 
    
   in making complicated expressions.  I'm sure that there are other 
   
   quirks, but until @{BOLD "Amiga Inc."} documents them, we're stymied.

   See Also, @{" FileExtFilter ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SetMacro" "Set Macro EnvVar... Menu Item:"

   This menuitem will change @{FG SHINE}MacroEnvVar@{FG TEXT} ToolType.  This is only used by 
   
   the nroff command to find macro files that are included in *NIX-type
   
   manual pages.

   See Also, @{" MacroEnvVar ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}
             @{" nroff.guide " LINK "NRoff"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SuperMAN" "SuperMAN.guide... Menu Item:"
@PREV "Menus"
   This menu item will make the program display this documentation.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "NRoff" "NRoff.guide... Menu Item:"
@PREV "Menus"

   This menu item will make the program display documentation for nroff.
   
   @{" Show me the nroff guide! " LINK "nroff.guide/main"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ToolTypes" "SuperMANPPC ToolTypes:"
@NEXT "Main"

   The following Default ToolTypes are used by this program:


      @{FG SHINE}ParentDir@{FG TEXT}     = RAM:
 
      @{FG SHINE}DirListFile@{FG TEXT}   = DocsDirList.txt @{" Show contents " SYSTEM "multiview DocsDirList.txt"}

      @{FG SHINE}CmdListFile@{FG TEXT}   = CommandsList.txt @{" Show contents " SYSTEM "multiview CommandsList.txt"}

      @{FG SHINE}FileEditor@{FG TEXT}    = C:Ed

      @{FG SHINE}MacroEnvVar@{FG TEXT}   = T:tmac (leave off the trailing slash!)
 
      @{FG SHINE}NRoffCommand@{FG TEXT}  = nroff -man

      @{FG SHINE}FileViewer@{FG TEXT}    = MultiView

      @{FG SHINE}FileExtFilter@{FG TEXT} = (#?.doc@{FG SHINE}|@{FG TEXT}#?.guide)

   Change them to suit yourself, but be careful with the @{BOLD FileExtFilter}
   
   ToolType.  The ASL File Requester & AmigaDOS-C functions used within
   
   the program expect the parentheses to be around the expression if you
   
   use the @{FG SHINE}@{B}|@{UB}@{FG TEXT} in making complicated expressions.  I'm sure that
    
   there are other quirks, but until @{BOLD "Amiga Inc."} documents them, we're stymied.

@ENDNODE

